Lack of warning that diet drink has sweeteners prompts FDA action

Maharashtra FDA order prohibits Hardcastle Restaurants, which operates McDonaldâ€™s, from selling Coke Zero without mandatory warnings that it contains artificial sweeteners - aspartame and acesulfame. This means the beverage cannot be sold loose through dispensers in plastic cup. The order can be applicable to other carbonated drinks that contain artificial sweeteners 
